champ:Gnar a lol:Champion, owl:NamedIndividual ;
    lol:championId "Gnar" ;
    lol:championKey "150" ;
    lol:championName "Gnar" ;
    lol:championTitle "the Missing Link" ;
    lol:blurb "Gnar is a primeval yordle whose playful antics can erupt into a toddler's outrage in an instant, transforming him into a massive beast bent on destruction. Frozen in True Ice for millennia, the curious creature broke free and now hops about a changed..." ;
    lol:lore "Gnar is a primeval yordle whose playful antics can erupt into a toddler's outrage in an instant, transforming him into a massive beast bent on destruction. Frozen in True Ice for millennia, the curious creature broke free and now hops about a changed world he sees as exotic and wondrous. Delighted by danger, Gnar flings whatever he can at his enemies, be it his bonetooth boomerang, or a nearby building." ;
    lol:adaptiveType "Physical" ;
    lol:lastChanged "V25.16" ;
    lol:costBE "2400"^^xsd:integer ;
    lol:costRP "880"^^xsd:integer ;
    lol:allyTip "Managing your Rage is very important. Try to time out your transformations so you can get maximum benefit from both forms." ;
    lol:allyTip "Position yourself next to walls to bait your enemies into getting stunned by your ultimate." ;
    lol:allyTip "Know your strengths! Mini Gnar is fast, squishy, and has high sustained damage. Mega Gnar is slow, tough, and has high burst." ;
    lol:enemyTip "Gnar can't gain Rage for 15 seconds after he turns from big to little. Use this chance to engage on his team." ;
    lol:enemyTip "Gnar's animations and resource bar change as he gets closer to transforming.  " ;
    lol:enemyTip "Gnar's ultimate stuns if he hits you into a wall. Be careful when fighting him near one." ;
